<tt>Tue Oct 21 10:24:40 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
My experience with these organizations is that for the most part they created a watering hole for military drunks in dry counties.  Others are fine outfits.. doing good stuff.  A few are headed up by imposters who never served.<br>
Standards of excellence for each individual post is contingent upon the excellence of individual local members.<br>
I have been to a few great organizations.. and some not so good.<br>
I don't care for those who favor one branch of the service over another.. or advocate that one war was more glorious than another... or are rank conscious.  Too many favor a pecking order rather than a brotherhood.<br><br>
